HEADWORD: Kilogrammetre
<hw>Kil"o*gram*me`tre</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mech.)</fld>
<def>A measure of energy or work done, being the amount expended in
raising one kilogram through the height of one meter, in the latitude of
Paris.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

